Eurobank Full-Year Profit Drops on Greek Crisis, Recession

-- B y   M a r c u s   B e n s a s s o n
-- 
2011-02-24T16:33:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/eurobank-full-year-profit-drops-on-greek-crisis-recession-1-.html
  EFG Eurobank Ergasias SA , the
second-largest bank in  Greece , said profit fell last year as
deposits shrank during the recession.  Net income declined to 68 million euros ($93.8 million)
after paying a one-off tax, compared with profit of 305 million
euros a year earlier, according to an e-mailed statement from
the Athens-based lender today. The average estimate of 10
analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was for 2010 net income of 67.1
million euros.  Customer deposits declined to 44.4 billion euros from 46.8
billion euros in 2009. Deposits in Greece were 33 billion euros
last year, down from 37.1 billion euros the year before.  Net income from the bankâ€™s central and southeast Europe
operations was 32 million euros in 2010, compared with a net
loss of 44 million euros in 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
